{"id":"jeshurun","term":"Jeshurun","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A poetical name for the people of Israel, used in token of affection, meaning, “the dear upright people” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 32:15\">Deut. 32:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 33:5\">33:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 33:26\">26</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 44:2\">Isa. 44:2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Deuteronomy 32:15","Deuteronomy 33:5","Deuteronomy 33:26","Isaiah 44:2"]}